otion a two-month negotiating window aimed at resolving the core dispute between the two countries over Iran’s nuclear ambitions. The United States and Iran have reached an interim agreement on Tehran’s nuclear programme, setting in motion a two-month negotiating window aimed at resolving the core dispute between the two countries over Iran’s nuclear ambitions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/to-be-negotiated-usiran-interim-deal-defers-final-decision-on-tehrans-nuclear-future/articleshow/131817509.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/to-be-negotiated-usiran-interim-deal-defers-final-decision-on-tehrans-nuclear-future/articleshow/131817509.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-18T10:16:22+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131817575,imgsize-56040.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Like nuclear, they don't blow up planet’: Trump's U-turn on Iran missiles after deal takes effect]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131816449.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[President Trump defended a new US-Iran understanding on ballistic missiles, deeming it unfair for Tehran to be disarmed if regional rivals possess them. He differentiated missile threats from nuclear ones, suggesting a less urgent global risk. US forces will remain in the Gulf post-agreement, with follow-up talks planned.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/like-nuclear-they-dont-blow-up-planet-trumps-u-turn-on-iran-missiles-after-deal-takes-effect/articleshow/131816449.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/like-nuclear-they-dont-blow-up-planet-trumps-u-turn-on-iran-missiles-after-deal-takes-effect/art